 I had to redo the album today, I’d tweak some things here and there production-wise and apply some of my experience from the past 20 years. Still, the important songs like “Sk8er Boi” and “Complicated” rocked enough — they had the live guitar and drums — and “I’m With You” wasn’t too polished. On songs like “Unwanted” and “Losing Grip,” we really went all the way — no holding back. — \u003Cem>L.G.\u003C/em> "}]},{type:"section",body:[{type:"subhed",value:"\u003Cstrong>Chloë Sevigny\u003C/strong>, 49, actress, on “Kids” (1995)",className:"g-heading3block g-align-left"},{type:"diptych",value:{imageOne:{media:{assetType:"scoopImage",assetSlug:"100000009393427",breakpointName:void 0,assetErrors:[],__typename:"Image",sourceId:"100000009393427",url:"/imagepages/2024/04/04/t-magazine/18tmag-origins-slide-L7RW.html",uri:"nyt://image/e1ce44ec-7d00-53d7-8e12-0a222732ae16",lastModified:"2024-04-16T20:06:22.680Z",lastMajorModification:"2024-04-16T20:06:22.680Z",headline:{default:""},bylines:[],type:"image",caption:{text:"Sevigny at the Jersey Shore in 1995. The actress, who has appeared in over 50 features, recently shot “Bonjour Tristesse,” an upcoming adaptation of the 1954 Françoise Sagan novel."},altText:"Chloë Sevigny turns to face the camera. Behind her are various theme park attractions, including a ferris wheel and a carousel.",credit:"From left: Lila Lee-Morrison; © Shining Excalibur Pictures/courtesy of Everett Collection",summary:"",original:{width:3491,height:2388},imageType:"photo",crops:[{name:"MASTER",box:{y2:2388,y1:0,x2:3491,x1:0},bleed:null,renditions:[{width:600,url:"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/04/18/t-magazine/18tmag-origins-slide-L7RW/18tmag-origins-slide-L7RW-articleLarge.jpg",name:"articleLarge",height:410},{width:1024,url:"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/04/18/t-magazine/18tmag-origins-slide-L7RW/18tmag-origins-slide-L7RW-jumbo.jpg",name:"jumbo",height:700},{width:2048,url:"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/04/18/t-magazine/18tmag-orig