 myself, “You have to stop now and go to law school.” Luckily, the book came out of me very quickly and, in retrospect, became a description of six years I’d spent in New York. It was very easy because I’d obviously touched something that mattered to me. "},{type:"text",value:"I’ve never reread “Dancer” [about gay life in 1970s New York] so, while I’m sure that if I did, I’d revise, revise, revise, I can’t imagine changing any of it. The campy style of the letters that frame the book is probably outdated, which is a shame since I love camp. "},{type:"text",value:"I’ve learned since then that writing is basically unconscious, and you don’t get any smarter about it. Imagine a brain surgeon who didn’t learn from each operation? We’d be horrified. But when you sit down to write, you’re always wondering how to do it. — \u003Cem>L.G.\u003C/em>"}]},{type:"section",body:[{type:"ad",value:{id:68,size:void 0}}]},{type:"section",body:[{type:"diptych",value:{imageOne:{media:{assetType:"scoopImage",assetSlug:"100000009393462",breakpointName:void 0,assetErrors:[],__typename:"Image",sourceId:"100000009393462",url:"/imagepages/2024/04/04/t-magazine/18tmag-origins-slide-GWEY.html",uri:"nyt://image/0273a115-cb13-54f2-822a-6df9de3ec0a6",lastModified:"2024-04-15T20:22:23.847Z",lastMajorModification:"2024-04-15T20:22:23.847Z",headline:{default:""},bylines:[],type:"image",caption:{text:"Harry and Stein, of the rock band Blondie, in the U.K. in 1977. Stein’s memoir, “Under a Rock,” will be published in June."},altText:"Debbie Harry and Chris Stein stand on a staircase with a curved bannister and portraits hanging on wooden walls.",credit:"From left: Jeff Gilbert/Alamy Stock Photo; CBW/Alamy Stock Photo",summary:"",original:{width:2480,height:3519},imageType:"photo",crops:[{name:"MASTER",box:{y2:3479,y1:61,x2:2410,x1:34},bleed:null,renditions:[{width:600,url:"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/04/18/t-magazine/18tmag-origins-slide-GWEY/18tmag-origins-slide-GWEY-articleLarge-v2.jpg",name: