 [her first hit, “Water,” debuted on the Billboard Hot 100 in October]. Obviously, people believe, ‘Oh, I have to make just pop.’ But that’s boring to me. I want to sell what I know and love.”"},{type:"text",value:"\u003Cstrong>Why South African music has global appeal:\u003C/strong> “People say they can feel it, and that’s cool because \u003Cem>we\u003C/em> feel it. It’s very spiritual to us; it’s a genre we feel in our bodies. All these amapiano dance moves that everyone does, it’s not even dancers that come up with these moves — it’s just random people, drunk uncles in the corners of clubs. It’s organic, and I think people are looking for that genuine vibe.” — \u003Cem>E.L.\u003C/em>"},{type:"text",value:"Production: Shay Johnson Studio. Hair: Christina “Tina” Trammell. Makeup: Jamal Scott for YSL Beauty",className:"g-detailblock"}]},{type:"section",body:[{type:"sectionheader",body:[{type:"video",value:{media:{assetType:"scoopVideo",assetSlug:"100000009403325",breakpointName:void 0,assetErrors:[],__typename:"Video",sourceId:"100000009403325",url:"https://www.nytimes.com/video/embedded/t-magazine/100000009403325/illinoise-portrait.html",uri:"nyt://video/d888903a-905d-5468-9da9-c6241aa01552",lastModified:"2024-04-08T21:39:22.197Z",lastMajorModification:"2024-04-08T21:39:22.197Z",headline:{default:""},bylines:[{renderedRepresentation:"By Jason Schmidt",prefix:"By",creators:[{displayName:"Jason Schmidt",givenName:"",familyName:"",url:"https://www.nytimes.com/by/jason-schmidt",uri:"nyt://person/2341c2b5-521f-5c71-b657-6dbbd68bfced",bioUrl:"https://www.nytimes.com/by/jason-schmidt",honorificSuffix:"",honorificPrefix:"",description:"",promotionalMedia:null}]}],summary:"Peck (near center, in a black shirt), photographed at the Park Avenue Armory in Manhattan on Feb. 27, 2024, along with (top row, from left) the “Illinoise” musicians Kathy Halvorson and Jessica Tsang, the dancer Craig Salstein, the musician Brett Parnell, the dancers Byron Tittle and Christine Flores, the