 play will be about what it means to see ourselves in these macho cis men who often get hurt pretending to almost die for our entertainment — or something like that?"}]},{type:"section",body:[{type:"text",value:"\u003Cstrong>Lindsey Adelman,\u003C/strong> \u003Cem>55, designer\u003C/em>"},{type:"text",value:"I’m putting together a digital archive of my work and ephemera — about 30 years’ worth — revisiting everything from the sculpture I made as a student at RISD to the paper lights David Weeks and I sold for $25 to datebooks where I scribbled notes about things I wished would come true and then did. I hope it’ll encourage others to start something. I want them to understand, “Oh, this was the first step … this beautiful, finished thing was inspired by a piece of garbage dangling from a streetlamp.”"}]},{type:"section",body:[{type:"text",value:"\u003Cstrong>Elizabeth Diller,\u003C/strong> \u003Cem>69, architect, Diller Scofidio + Renfro\u003C/em>"},{type:"image",value:{media:{assetType:"scoopImage",assetSlug:"100000009397893",breakpointName:void 0,assetErrors:[],__typename:"Image",sourceId:"100000009397893",url:"/imagepages/2024/04/04/t-magazine/18tmag-ticker-slide-VMYO.html",uri:"nyt://image/21ec4e03-723e-5ba9-8a61-f999d0ed3f1d",lastModified:"2024-04-16T17:51:57.432Z",lastMajorModification:"2024-04-16T17:51:57.432Z",headline:{default:""},bylines:[],type:"image",caption:{text:""},altText:"A shadowy image of a blurred figure in an illuminated doorway at the top of some stairs.",credit:"David Wall/Getty Images",summary:"",original:{width:3000,height:2000},imageType:"photo",crops:[{name:"MASTER",box:{y2:2000,y1:0,x2:3000,x1:0},bleed:null,renditions:[{width:600,url:"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/04/18/t-magazine/18tmag-ticker-slide-VMYO/18tmag-ticker-slide-VMYO-articleLarge.jpg",name:"articleLarge",height:400},{width:1024,url:"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/04/18/t-magazine/18tmag-ticker-slide-VMYO/18tmag-ticker-slide-VMYO-jumbo.jpg",name:"jumbo",height:683